title: For Sale:  Lets kick the "craigslisters" off ARMSLIST use the FLAG button
postcontent:
ARMSLIST has been attacked by "spammers" looking to scam you or sell your phone number and email address to marketing agencies. This happened to craigslist several years ago and has been spreading to arms list over the past 2 years, ever since "the big scare"  I have made the mistake and responded to a a couple of these ads. within a few days get flooded with emails and marketing phone calls from all over the place. 

They ALL have 2 things in common and that makes it easy to spot their ads. 
1) they are all "unregistered"
2) there is no phone number in their ads

however, there is other things that set them apart. The price seems unreasonably low, they have multiple ads for hard to find items or items in strong demand, no photos, offers to trade you for your lower price items, etc.

we can only do this if we band together and flag these ads. Thank you.

GOD BLESS AMERICA
WE NEED ALL THE HELP WE CAN GET



TRUST ME... IT DIDNT USTA BE THIS WAY. BACK IN 2010 THIS PLACE WAS FULL OF GREATNESS. I KNOW IT IS HARD TO UNDERSTAND IF YOU ARE NEW TO ARMSLIST BUT ITS THE TRUTH. ASK ANYONE THAT HAS BEEN A MEMBER SINCE BEFORE DEC. OF 2012

title: For Sale:  50 Caliber Connecticut Valley Arms Bobcat
postcontent:
This is a muzzle loading rifle just like in the olden days. But with a twist. You can fire it the old way or the new way. For the old way, you soak your patches, cast your lead balls in a mold, fix your primer to the bullet, insert your percussion cap, pour in your pre-measured black powder and off you go. Just like in the olden days with all the smoke and noise. For the new way, you can use the speed loaders with rifled bullets just like the snipers use. You purchase pre-made patches, bullets, etc and just pour everything in to the speed loader.

This rifle is perfect for those hunters wanting a more intimate hunting experience. You get one shot. A lot of hunters feel that type of shooting is more fair to the animal. Whether you use the speed loaders or do it old school, it's traditional shooting. Power? It's 50 caliber folks. 44 magnum ain't got nothin on a 50. This round will stop the most determined pig/hog and with the rifled barrel, your accuracy is pretty much guaranteed.

This looks like your great grandfather's rifle, but isn't. The rifle has a composite (not wooden) stock and all metal barrel and mechanism parts. The military style blade sights give a great sight picture in low light. Easy to clean and maintain. The weight of the rifle is pretty substantial and takes a lot of the kick, so it's a comfortable rifle to fire and carry. The blued finish is easy to keep clean. Comes with a carry bag/case.

I am looking to sell it for $200 (or best offer) or trade for a hand gun. If you have a pistol you no longer use and would like to offer me in exchange, let me know. Text me ONLY at: REDACTED, that way your offer/question will have a date stamp and as it's first come, first served, you'll be at the head of the line. Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  NIGHTHAWK CUSTOM T4 9MM
postcontent: Nighthawk Custom is excited not only about the Model T4 for what we designed it as but what the response has been from the consumer market. The 9mm cartridge in a 1911 designed for concealed carry may be the best of both worlds when it comes to muzzle controllability and magazine capacity in a 1911. The T4 contains some of the most evolutionary features offered by the company. The T4 resembles the popular T3, but on a 3.8” barrel platform. Reliability was the most important consideration when plans for the new pistol began, hence the 3.8” Nighthawk match grade barrel over the more popular but less reliable 3.5” or shorter barrel. The proven Bob Marvel Everlast® Recoil System was modified to fit into the smaller T4 frame, thus reducing felt recoil and decreasing recovery time between shots. The frame is thinned just like Nighthawks popular Lady Hawk. The proprietary barrel is crowned and recessed with the slide. On the outside, the front of the slide has cuts designed to reduce weight. They taper in towards the crowned barrel, giving a unique look to the T4 like no other handgun produced by Nighthawk. Grips are like the T3 and are thinned for less bulk.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Romainan contract vz.24 sniper 8mm
postcontent:
Czech built contract Romanian vz.24 BRNO Mauser sniper with mounting bases, but no scope mount or scope. Serial - DR 37xx. Parts are mismatched, this is normal for Romanian contract snipers because these guns were not originally built as snipers, but rather converted from standard vz.24 models at the factory. Parts are all Czech built and nothing looks replaced since the war. Finish is worn pretty good with very minor pitting in some areas on the surface. Stock looks like it has never been sanded and has a lot of character. It has some disassembly marks on the magazine floor plate. Import marked on the bottom of barrel. Original Czech Factory turned down bolt. Has cleaning rod. You can still see the top of the crest on the receiver from before it was converted into a sniper by the Czechs. Bore looks great, clean, no pitting. Iron sights can be used through the scope block mounts.

Scope mounts are hard to find. But not impossible. Originals and repros pop up every now and then on Gunbroker, ebay, or at gun shows.
I got more pictures

Tags
/k/ Mauser 8mm vz-24 vz24 sniper bolt-action ww2 wwII
